creator: BiblioCommons
descriptionHtml:
Olathe Public Library’s Mobile App makes it easy to find and discover titles, manage your account, and get the location and title availability information you need.

Features:
• quickly and accurately search the collection
• get details on any title, including descriptions and community events
• check a title’s availability – even map the locations where it is currently available
• place holds
• manage your account: check to see if holds are ready, renew titles, suspend holds, or instantly see the date your next title is due
• add a title to your “For Later” list
• browse bestsellers, new titles, and recent reviews
• check neighborhood library hours and get directions to the nearest Olathe Public Library location
descriptionShort: Keep the library in your pocket!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: This is release includes behind the scenes changes, and small user interface adjustments.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
The Olathe Public Library app has been rebuilt from the ground up for you to discover new titles, plan your next visit, and browse recommendations curated by your library staff.

The app includes some great new features!

- Clean modern design
- A new search screen that groups titles by format
- Lists of great titles created by your library staff
- Personalized elements to show information relevant to you
- Opening hours and details of your favourite library locations

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
You can now filter your search results by topic, genre, and content type.

The number of applied filters now displays on the Filter screens.

We have refined the display of the My Settings screen, and added an About This App screen.

You can now unregister your account from the app.

This release also includes smaller UX improvements as well as behind the scenes accessibility enhancements, improvements, and bug fixes.
